E-mail:   PrivacyPolicy@applinic.com <br><br>

<h5> Privacy of Children's Information.</h5> Children’s accounts are registered under their parents’ or guardians’ account for the family. We do not knowingly collect information from children under the age of 13 years. Such family accounts should be operated by adults on behalf of children when they need to access healthcare. We strongly recommend that minors under the age of 18 ask their parents for permissionbefore sending any personal health information to anyone over the Internet, or better still to assist themfor any clerking, treatment and video conference sessions. <br>

<h5>Links to Third-Party Sites.</h5> We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of third-party sites that ours may be linked to. You should review the policies of other sites to ensure they meet your personal privacy expectations for your own protection.<br><br>

<h5>Changeability of Our Privacy Policy. </h5>
We regularly review this Privacy Policy and may alter, change, modify, add, or remove portions as necessary. If we change this Privacy Policy in ways that affect how we use your personal medical practice or company information, we will notify you here or on our home page. We encourage you to keep yourself updated on these changes from time to time by visiting this page regularly. 


